efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n * (forget - delay))
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a 1-D DP array where dp[i] is the number of new people who learn the secret on day i. For each day, sum the active sharers from the sliding window [day-forget+1, day-delay]. The final answer is the sum of the last (forget-1) days, as those people still remember.

